            <mixed-citation publication-type="journal">Nisly SA, Ray SM, Moye RA. Tobramycin-induced hepatotoxicity. Ann Pharmacother 2007; 41: 2061-5. <annotation><p><italic toggle="yes">(Patient with pseudomonas bacteremia treated with multiple antibiotics, developed elevations in AST [970 U/L], ALT [315 U/L] and Alk P [432 U/L] and mild jaundice within days of starting tobramycin; changing antibiotics did not affect enzyme elevations until tobramycin was stopped with resolution in 1-2 weeks; apparently no symptoms or allergic signs).</italic></p></annotation><pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">17956959</pub-id></mixed-citation>
          </ref>
